On the lateroplantar margin of the body there is a rough and proximodistally developed fusiform surface, typical of this metatarsal, which is probably the attachment area for the long plantar ligament (
Barone 2010b
). The distal head of the Mt IV is globular as in other metapodials, being just slightly asymmetric.
